entry.title: WEATHER ADVISORY , Killarney
entry.summary: Persons in or near this area should be on the lookout for adverse weather conditions and take necessary safety precautions. Issued: 10:00 PM EST Friday 27 January 2023

entry.title: Friday night: Snow. Low minus 7.
entry.summary: Mainly cloudy. 60 percent chance of flurries early this evening. Snow and local blowing snow beginning early this evening then changing to 40 percent chance of flurries overnight. Amount 5 to 10 cm. Wind south 50 km/h gusting to 70 becoming west 40 gusting to 60 late this evening. Low minus 7. Wind chill minus 16 overnight. Forecast issued 4:00 PM EST Friday 27 January 2023

entry.title: Saturday: Chance of flurries. Temperature steady near minus 7. POP 40%
entry.summary: A mix of sun and cloud. 40 percent chance of flurries early in the morning. Wind west 30 km/h gusting to 50 becoming light early in the afternoon. Temperature steady near minus 7. Wind chill minus 16 in the morning and minus 8 in the afternoon. UV index 1 or low. Forecast issued 4:00 PM EST Friday 27 January 2023

entry.title: Saturday night: Periods of snow. Low minus 12. POP 40%
